      • getCategoryLabels

        public final Iterable<String> getCategoryLabels()
        Gets the chart's category labels. If category labels are not set neither as cell range reference nor as direct value, automatic labels will be used (sequence of integral numbers starting from 1 whose count will be equal to the count of values in the first chart series).
        Returns:
        The chart's category labels.

      • getCategoryLabelsReference

        public final String getCategoryLabelsReference()
        Gets the chart's category labels as a cell range reference (for example, 'Sheet1!A1:D1'). Values from cells in the referenced range will be used as category labels.
        Returns:
        The chart's category labels as a cell range reference.

      • selectData

        public final void selectData(CellRange range,
                             boolean switchRowColumn,
                             boolean excludeCategoryLabels)
        Selects the data for the chart.
        Parameters:
        range - The cell range which contains data for the chart.
        switchRowColumn - if set to true category labels will be in first column (not row), series names will be in first row (not column) and series values will be in columns (not rows).
        excludeCategoryLabels - if set to true, category labels won't be resolved from range.
